\pard\pardeftab720\sa150\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf4 Transition:   We learn at a young age to not be who really are don\'92t we?\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa150\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

\fs36 \cf2 WE\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa150\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls1\ilvl0
\f1\b0\fs24 \cf2 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}We all pretend and have been since we were younger.\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}We weren\'92t made to pretend\'85we were made to be known!\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa150\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls1\ilvl0
\f0\b \cf5 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}And the place that should have the answer to this problem is the worse place in the world\'85the church!\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa150\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\cf5 \
\pard\pardeftab720\pardirnatural\qc\partightenfactor0

\f2\b0\fs21 \cf6 Carey Nieuwhof\
\
But I wonder how many Christians actually take time to confess their sins, deeply and personally.\
\
In a culture in which\'a0self is continually elevated and celebrated, how do you get to a place where in humility you realize you are not who you hoped to be and not what you could be?\
\
How does\'a0confession happen\'a0in a generation that has been convinced that they are awesome and everyone else (the school system, the neighbors, the other kids, the government, that bully) is the problem?\
\
We seem to be great at blaming. Great at judging. \ul (we) are more like the Pharisees than we are like Jesus\ulnone .\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa150\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\cf6 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa150\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf4 Transition:  This morning I want to look at a passage that I hope will help us see why confession and being real is important to God and should be important to us.\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa150\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

\fs36 \cf2 GOD\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa150\pardirnatural\qc\partightenfactor0
\cf7 20\'a0
\f2\b0\fs24 Now Abraham moved on from there\'a0into the region of the Negev\'a0and lived between Kadesh\'a0and Shur.\'a0For a while\'a0he stayed in Gerar,\'a0
\f0\b\fs18 \super 2\'a0
\f2\b0\fs24 \nosupersub and there Abraham said of his wife Sarah, \'93She is my sister.\'94 Then Abimelek\'a0king of Gerar sent for Sarah and took her.\

\f0\b\fs18 \super 3\'a0
\f3\b0\fs24 \nosupersub But God came to Abimelek\'a0in a dream\'a0one night and said to him, \'93You are as good as dead\'a0because of the woman you have taken; she is a married woman.\'94\

\f0\b\fs18 \super 4\'a0
\f3\b0\fs24 \nosupersub Now Abimelek had not gone near her, so he said, \'93Lord, will you destroy an innocent nation?\'a0
\f0\b\fs18 \super 5\'a0
\f3\b0\fs24 \nosupersub Did he not say to me, \'91She is my sister,\'92 and didn\'92t she also say, \'91He is my brother\'92? I have done this with a clear conscience\'a0and clean hands.\'94\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa150\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls2\ilvl0\cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}Hold up God\'85I didn\'92t do anything wrong!\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa150\pardirnatural\qc\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs18 \cf7 \super 6\'a0
\f3\b0\fs24 \nosupersub Then God said to him in the dream, \'93Yes, I know you did this with a clear conscience, and so I have kept\'a0you from sinning against me.\'a0That is why I did not let you touch her.\'a0
\f0\b\fs18 \super 7\'a0
\f3\b0\fs24 \nosupersub Now return the man\'92s wife, for he is a prophet,\'a0and he will pray for you\'a0and you will live. But if you do not return her, you may be sure that you and all who belong to you will die.\'94\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa150\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls3\ilvl0\cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}God says \'91Yeah I know, but this is warning and if you don\'92t do what I\'92m telling you, I will kill you\'92.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa150\pardirnatural\qc\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs18 \cf7 \super 8\'a0
\f3\b0\fs24 \nosupersub Early the next morning Abimelek summoned all his officials, and when he told them all that had happened, they were very much afraid.\'a0
\f0\b\fs18 \super 9\'a0
\f3\b0\fs24 \nosupersub Then Abimelek called Abraham in and said, \'93What have you done to us? How have I wronged you that you have brought such great guilt upon me and my kingdom? You have done things to me that should never be done.\'94\'a0
\f0\b\fs18 \super 10\'a0
\f3\b0\fs24 \nosupersub And Abimelek asked Abraham, \'93What was your reason for doing this?\'94\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa150\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls4\ilvl0\cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}Abraham is busted!\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa150\pardirnatural\qc\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs18 \cf7 \super 11\'a0
\f3\b0\fs24 \nosupersub Abraham replied, \'93I said to myself, \'91There is surely no fear of God\'a0in this place, and they will kill me because of my wife.\'92\'a0\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa150\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls5\ilvl0\cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}He blames the victims here!\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}This is what our culture does today.\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}Now this next verse needs a whole lot of explaining here this morning\'85\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa150\pardirnatural\qc\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs18 \cf7 \super 12\'a0
\f3\b0\fs24 \nosupersub Besides, she really is my sister,\'a0the daughter of my father though not of my mother; and she became my wife.\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa150\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls6\ilvl0\cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}Um yeah\'85so weren\'92t going to touch that verse today.\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}The whole sister-wives issues we\'92ll deal with later\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa150\pardirnatural\qc\partightenfactor0
\cf7 \'a0
\f0\b\fs18 \super 13\'a0
\f3\b0\fs24 \nosupersub And when God had me wander\'a0from my father\'92s household,\'a0\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa150\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls7\ilvl0\cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}Now it is God\'92s fault he did this\'85you ever blame God?\
\pard\tx940\tx1440\pardeftab720\li1440\fi-1440\sa150\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls7\ilvl1\cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}God if my spouse were nicer I could love her more\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}If I made more money or had a better job I could give more back to you\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}If I didn\'92t have all these emotional problems you gave at a young age I\'92d be more stable in life.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa150\pardirnatural\qc\partightenfactor0
\cf7 I said to her, \'91This is how you can show your love to me: Everywhere we go, say of me, \'93He is my brother.\'94\'92\'94\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa150\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls8\ilvl0\cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}I just want to pause for a moment and ask \'96 ladies\'85how many of you want to be married to this guy?\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}Now this is where the story gets weird for me in a big way!\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}Because if you\'92re the king and this guy wronged you how do you feel toward him right now?  What do you want to do to him?  \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa150\pardirnatural\qc\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs18 \cf7 \super 14\'a0
\f3\b0\fs24 \nosupersub Then Abimelek\'a0brought sheep and cattle and male and female slaves and gave them to Abraham, and he returned Sarah his wife to him.\'a0
\f0\b\fs18 \super 15\'a0
\f3\b0\fs24 \nosupersub And Abimelek said, \'93My land is before you; live wherever you like.\'94\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa150\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls9\ilvl0\cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}This is bizarre to me and makes no sense in our culture.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa150\pardirnatural\qc\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs18 \cf7 \super 16\'a0
\f3\b0\fs24 \nosupersub To Sarah he said, \'93I am giving your brother a thousand shekels\'a0of silver. This is to cover the offense against you before all who are with you; you are completely vindicated.\'94\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa150\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls10\ilvl0\cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}It is valued today at roughly $320,000.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa150\pardirnatural\qc\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs18 \cf7 \super 17\'a0
\f3\b0\fs24 \nosupersub Then Abraham prayed to God,\'a0and God healed Abimelek, his wife and his female slaves so they could have children again,\'a0
\f0\b\fs18 \super 18\'a0
\f3\b0\fs24 \nosupersub for the\'a0Lord\'a0had kept all the women in Abimelek\'92s household from conceiving because of Abraham\'92s wife Sarah.\
\pard\pardeftab720\pardirnatural\qc\partightenfactor0
\cf7 \
\pard\pardeftab720\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

\f4\b\fs28 \cf4 Transition:  This is a bizarre story and confused me for years until recently.  Because it seems like Abraham lied and God blessed him for it!\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

\fs36 \cf0 YOU\
\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls11\ilvl0
\f3\b0\fs24 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}Here is what I realized this week though:\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}God wasn\'92t rewarding him for lying\'85but finally being honest and revealing who he really is.\
\pard\tx940\tx1440\pardeftab720\li1440\fi-1440\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls11\ilvl1\cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}God is telling us through this story he can\'92t do anything with us as long as we are hiding behind who we think culture wants us to be instead of who we really are!\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls11\ilvl0\cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}God wants his church to be filled with people who are real and honest about who they really are\'85not who they want people to think they are.\
\pard\pardeftab720\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

\f4\b\fs28 \cf4 Transition:  But there is something else too!\
\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls12\ilvl0
\f3\b0\fs24 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}The kings name is Abimelek which means = My Dad is King\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}But the more I thought about it\'85it hit me\'85there is another guy in the Bible who goes around telling everyone My Dad is King too!\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}What I really want you to know today while Abimelek was able to bless Abraham financially because He was real and honest, we have Jesus who wants to bless us immeasurably more than we can imagine the moment we are honest about who we really are in His sight.\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}Today there are people in this room who are pretending to be one thing but really aren\'92t\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}Today there are people in this room who are trying to be good enough and think that the way to God is to be good but their not and so they have to pretend and I\'92m here to today to tell you that the Good News of Jesus is you don\'92t have to keep pretending you\'92re something you\'92re not. \
\pard\tx940\tx1440\pardeftab720\li1440\fi-1440\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls12\ilvl1\cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}You\'92re already accepted\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}You\'92re already welcomed\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}You\'92re already wanted\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}You\'92re already loved by God\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls12\ilvl0\cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}All you have to do is be real with God\'85that\'92s it!\
\pard\pardeftab720\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \
\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls13\ilvl0\cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}Heads bowed and eyes closed \'96 there are people here today who need to be real with who they are with God and even themselves.\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}If today you recognize I need to be real, I need to quit pretending, I need to start being real with who I am and how God see\'92s me.\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}I want you to pray this prayer with me\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}Pray now to g\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}Heavenly father\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}I am a sinner\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}In need of a savior\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}I believe that Jesus Christ is the son of God, the perfect son of God, the savior of the world\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}I believe that He died for my sin on a cross\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}I repent of my sin\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}I will be real\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}I will accept your gift of eternal life\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}I accept you\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}I will follow you as you live in me all of the days of my life\
\pard\pardeftab720\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \
If you came back to God or gave your life today for the first time I want you to raise your hand on the count of three\'85one two three!\
\
\
How do I do that?\
\
\
Transition to communion!\
}